The Search box on top-right corner allows me to make a search from any JIRA page. The results are always shown on the same page and the page that I am currently on is lost. In order to make a search on a new page (or tab) I have to open a new one, wait for the page to load and make the search on that page which makes me lose a few seconds each time. Also a few more clicks.

Please also note that most browsers open links in a new tab when clicked with Ctrl key pressed.

Suggestion: Currently, search box makes the search with "Enter" key. When "Ctrl + Enter" is used, search results should open in a new tab, thus eliminating the overhead.

