In JIRA, we have the option to [clone issues|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRASOFTWARECLOUD/Creating+issues+and+sub-tasks#Creatingissuesandsub-tasks-Cloninganissue] which will also retrieve the custom fields. 

However, if some of the custom fields are retrieved from third-party add-ons, the clone will not include these specific fields, probably because it's related to the add-on or its configuration does not match with the ones from the bundled custom fields in our issues. For example, the [Issue Checklist add-on|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.gebsun.plugins.jira.issuechecklist/cloud/overview] which will bring a custom field called *Checklist*. This will not be included in the cloned issue.

This is a suggestion to allow the custom fields retrieved by third-party add-ons to be included in cloned issues. :)
